    <string name="info_gehrung">Calculates angles Alpha and Beta for a compound miter from angle Gamma and side lengths A and B.</string>
    <string name="info_schnittgeschwindigkeit">Calculates cutting speed Vc from tool diameter and RPM. Formula: Vc = π × D × n / 60,000. Green = within recommended range.</string>
    <string name="info_zahnvorschub">Calculates feed per tooth fz. Formula: fz = (V × 1000) / (N × Z).</string>
    <string name="info_kantenmaterial">Calculates remaining length of edge banding on a roll. Formula: Length = π × (ØA² − Øb²) / (4 × S × 1000).</string>
    <string name="info_plattenmaterial">Calculates panel weight from dimensions and material-specific weight factor.</string>
    <string name="info_goldener_schnitt">The Golden Ratio divides a line so that the larger segment (Major) relates to the smaller (Minor) as the total relates to the larger. Factor: 1.618.</string>
    <string name="info_holzschwund">Calculates wood shrinkage based on wood species and moisture change. Radial = across grain, Tangential = along growth rings.</string>
